The assistant should consider the following criteria when predicting the species:
- Iris setosa: sepal length and width are typically shorter and narrower, petal length and width are shorter and more uniform
- Iris versicolor: sepal length and width are typically longer and wider, petal length and width are longer and more variable
- Iris virginica: sepal length and width are typically longer and wider, petal length and width are longer and more uniform

